Justice Abdul Dogo of the federal high court in Akure, Ondo State, has been kidnapped by gunmen while travelling from Abuja to Akure. He was abducted on Tuesday. In a swift effort to rescue the judge, the Inspector General of Police has deployed a special team of policemen to Akure. SaharaReporters learnt that the kidnappers demanded N50 million for the release of the judge.Details later.